{"sha": "5bbfea03ccada14bbaca6df6c0ef3760ac44a9a5", "node_id": "C_kwDOAAsO6NoAKDViYmZlYTAzY2NhZGExNGJiYWNhNmRmNmMwZWYzNzYwYWM0NGE5YTU", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Aleksey Kladov", "email": "aleksey.kladov@gmail.com", "date": "2022-10-08T22:18:11Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Aleksey Kladov", "email": "aleksey.kladov@gmail.com", "date": "2022-10-08T22:25:13Z"}, "message": "fix: in VSCode, correctly resolve relative paths to errors\n\nVS Code problem matcher are restricted to be static \"regexes\". You can't\ncreate a problem matcher dynamically, and you can't use custom code in\nlieu of problem matcher.\n\nThis creates a problem for rust/cargo compiler errors. They use paths\nrelative to the root of the Cargo workspace, but VS Code doesn't\nnecessary know where that root is.\n\nLuckily, there's a way out: our current problem matcher is defined like\nthis:\n\n    \"fileLocation\": [ \"autoDetect\", \"${workspaceRoot}\" ],\n\nThat means that relative pahts would be resoleved relative to workspace\nroot. VS Code allows to specify a command inside `${}`. So we can plug\ncustom logic there to fetch Cargo's workspace root!\n\nAnd that's exactly what this PR is doing!", "tree": {"sha": "63f1d3a2957edc137970f90ceadb5ee675816d53", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/63f1d3a2957edc137970f90ceadb5ee675816d53"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/5bbfea03ccada14bbaca6df6c0ef3760ac44a9a5", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/5bbfea03ccada14bbaca6df6c0ef3760ac44a9a5", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/5bbfea03ccada14bbaca6df6c0ef3760ac44a9a5", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/5bbfea03ccada14bbaca6df6c0ef3760ac44a9a5/comments", "author": {"login": "matklad", "id": 1711539, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE3MTE1Mzk=", "avatar_url": "https://avat